RACE.RACE_TEXT: Alberta Sire Debutante S. CENTURY MILE RACE 7 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 78. Stakes Purse 50000. A STAKE FOR THREE-YEAR-OLD FILLIES WHO ARE BY A STALLION THAT STOOD IN ALBERTA FOR THE 2019 BREEDING SEASON. A fee of $100.00 required to nominate. A payment of $500.00 is required to pass the entry box and an additional $400.00 is required to start. The purse will be divided $30,000 to the owner of the winner, $10,000 to the second place finisher, $5,000 to the third place finisher, $2,500 to the fourth place finisher and $1,000 to the fifth place finisher. A payment of $500.00 will be paid to all horses who start and finish sixth or worse. Thefield will be limited to 12 starters. Preference will be given to those horses with the highest lifetime earnings. A trophy will be presented to the winning owner. Weight 122 lbs., Maidens allowed 3 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ECHO CREEK saved ground early while four wide, advanced quickly in the final turn, set sight on SINGING BELL, and won driving. BRYNN'S DREAM trailed the field, drove inside at the head of the lane, chased under heavy urging, dueled, and inched up. HERMANITA ALEX settled inside early, lacked running room at the head of the stretch, and yielded. LILLY'S OF LONDON stalked the early pacesetters, and faded inside. FASTESTGIRLINTOWN dueled outside of SINGING BELL, was unable to move on with rival in the far turn, and faltered.

CRUZ sped clear early, saw margins diminish nearing the quarter pole, drifted down to the rail off the final turn, dueled inside of DANZA UNBRIDLED and was out finished.
